# Single Tweet Patterns

## Pattern 1: Bold Claim

{Strong, concise opinion or observation.}

{Optional: one sentence of supporting evidence or context.}

---

## Pattern 2: Question

{Specific, interesting question that invites replies.}

{Optional: your own answer or a constraint that makes the question harder.}

---

## Pattern 3: Stat + Insight

{Surprising statistic or data point.}

{One sentence explaining why it matters or what it implies.}

---

## Pattern 4: Contrarian Take

{Challenge a common belief directly.}

{1-2 sentences of reasoning. Do not just state the take -- show why you hold it.}

---

## Pattern 5: Micro-Story

{A complete story in 280 characters: setup, conflict, resolution.}

{The shorter, the better. Every word earns its place.}

---

## Pattern 6: Observation + Implication

{Something you noticed -- specific, concrete, grounded in experience.}

{What it means or what it suggests about a larger trend.}

---

## Usage Notes

- Pick the pattern that fits your message. Do not force content into the wrong shape.
- Test readability: if you have to reread your own tweet to understand it, simplify.
- One idea per tweet. If you have two ideas, write two tweets.
- End on the strong word. Restructure the sentence so the most impactful word is last.
